<title>UK: BP chairman still in talks for UK gov't job.</title>
<headline>BP chairman still in talks for UK gov't job.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Sir David Simon, chairman of British Petroleum Co Plc, is still in talks to take up a position in Britain's new Labour government, BP said on Tuesday.</p>
<p>&quot;Talks with with Blair's office are still going on,&quot; a BP spokesman told journalists after BP released its first-quarter results earlier today.</p>
<p>Kennedy said he did not know what position was being discussed.</p>
<p>The Financial Times on Saturday reported that new prime minister Tony Blair had offered Simon the post of minister for Europe, but this position was later taken up by Doug Henderson.</p>
<p>Simon, recently voted British businessman of the year, is widely accredited for turning round BP in the early 1990s.</p>
